'''Virtue names''', also known as '''grace names''', are used as [[personal name]]s in a number of cultures. In the English-speaking world, the [[Puritans]] commonly expressed their values through creative names, many in the form of virtue names like Grace, Felicity, Chastity or Hope.<ref>{{cite book|last=Bardsley|first=Charles|title=Curiosities of Puritan Nomenclature|year=1888|publisher=Chatto and Windus|location=London|url=http://publicdomainreview.org/2012/09/18/curiosities-of-puritan-nomenclature-1888/}}</ref> These names have entered the standard British and American usage, without the religious connection.

Virtue names, such as [[Iman (concept)|Iman]], can also be found in the Islamic world.{{fact|date=June 2015}}

